#week-title("Four", "Desoille's Day: The Citrinitas & Inner Conjunction")

=== Core Teaching

Repeated cohobation elevates the preparation. As the salt absorbs more and more
of the essence, the resulting body becomes noticeably more alive and fragrant.

This week also introduces the second major transition in the inner work: from the
Dawn (Albedo) to *The Day* (Citrinitas). This is the stage of ascension where
imagery becomes mythological or archetypal, and the solar warmth begins to assert
itself.

=== Topics This Week

- The elevating power of repeated cohobation
- Characteristics of the Citrinitas (Yellowing)
- Preparation for Month 11: Medicinal ethics

#inner-work[
  *The Citrinitas Waking Dream*

  In your waking dream practice this month, begin your ascent deliberately.
  Starting from the Dawn state, allow the imagery to rise further.

  Notice when images lose their personal character and become symbolic, universal,
  and luminous. A solar quality — warmth without harshness — characterises this
  zone. When you encounter it, remain there. This corresponds to the moment when
  the cohobation produces a unified and potentized medicine. Record the quality
  of the light in your journal.
]

